<div class="panel panel-info">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">PT MACS Manual</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
   <ul class="list-group">
  	<li class="list-group-item">The Physical Therapist Manual for the Assessment of Clinical Skills (PT MACS) is a clinical skills assessment document that has been developed by clinical and academic faculty.</li>
    <li class="list-group-item">Its format is similar to The Blue MACS, an assessment tool in use since 1977.</li>
    <li class="list-group-item">A task force comprised of ACCEs, DCEs and clinicians was charged with developing the content and format of the new PT MACS.</li>

   </ul>
  </div>
</div>



<div class="panel panel-info">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">Skill Content</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
   <ul class="list-group">
  	<li class="list-group-item">The skill content of the PT MACS is based upon definitions for professional behaviors identified as the Generic Abilities1 and clinical practice as outlined in A Normative Model of Physical Therapist Professional Education2-3 and The Guide to Physical Therapist Practice 4-6. </li>
  	<li class="list-group-item">The PT MACS is designed to be used as a method for evaluating clinical performance and as a tool to promote clinical teaching and learning.</li>
  	<li class="list-group-item">It identifies skills every student needs to develop in order to be considered entry-level. </li>
  	<li class="list-group-item">Clinical Instructors (CIs) and students can also use the PT MACS to collaborate in developing a successful clinical learning experience.</li>
   </ul>
  </div>
</div>


<div class="panel panel-info">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">Draft Version 1.0</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
   <ul class="list-group">
  	<li class="list-group-item">Draft version 1.0 of the PT MACS was piloted in 2001 by several member programs of The Consortium.</li>
  	<li class="list-group-item">Based on feedback from CIs draft versions 2.0 and 3.0 were created in 2002.</li>
  	<li class="list-group-item">Member programs of The Consortium participated in the piloting of the PT MACS between 2001-2003.</li>
  	<li class="list-group-item">The first edition of the PT MACS was published in April 2004.</li>

   </ul>
  </div>
</div>


